1
00:00:14,359 --> 00:00:16,000
When was it exactly

2
00:00:16,719 --> 00:00:18,120
that I started being unable

3
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,440
to take my eyes off him?

4
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:56,400
"Feel What You Feel"

5
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:59,100
(Episode 2: Let's be best friends, okay?)

6
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,599
Senior!
You're here too?

7
00:02:02,439 --> 00:02:03,439
Let's go.

8
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:12,000
Hello, judges.

9
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:15,360
I'm Li Ming, a freshman
from the Law School.

10
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:18,560
I'll be singing "Courage" by Fish Leong

11
00:02:18,879 --> 00:02:20,479
for everyone.

12
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:24,120
We all need courage

13
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:26,479
to face the rumors.

14
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,198
Finding the courage

15
00:02:28,199 --> 00:02:31,000
to hold you tight...

16
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:33,439
our love is worth it.

17
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:36,120
Okay, that's enough.

18
00:02:37,639 --> 00:02:38,918
Wait, Professor!

19
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:40,638
It's just... what I had for dinner

20
00:02:40,639 --> 00:02:41,918
was a bit too salty.

21
00:02:41,919 --> 00:02:43,360
I don't usually sound like this.

22
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,039
Professor,

23
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:45,359
could I have one more chance?

24
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,319
That won't be necessary.
Thanks for coming.

25
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:58,879
You're done?

26
00:02:59,319 --> 00:03:00,319
How'd it go?

27
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:01,879
Me?

28
00:03:02,159 --> 00:03:03,520
I just read a poem

29
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,039
and blew them away.

30
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,159
You should've seen it...

31
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,680
the judge held my hand and said,

32
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,280
"Yu Lei,

33
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:11,879
we've been waiting so long for you!"

34
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,560
Passing was a piece of cake.

35
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,479
By the way,

36
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:17,520
what were you laughing at?

37
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:22,120
Oh, just the students
auditioning today.

38
00:03:22,159 --> 00:03:23,039
They're awful.

39
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,919
There was this one guy who was even worse.

40
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,280
He looked like a gorilla

41
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:29,198
and sang "Courage."

42
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:30,839
I have no idea who gave him the courage

43
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,280
to sing that badly.

44
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,438
And then there was this
guy who looked like a poodle.

45
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:38,840
He tried to breakdance,

46
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,158
but as soon as he got on stage,

47
00:03:40,159 --> 00:03:41,359
he just fell flat on his face.

48
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,598
That was a floor move!

49
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:44,776
You clearly don't know anything.

50
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,439
Floor move? More like mopping the floor.

51
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,800
You...

52
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:50,840
Li Ming, Ouyang Han,

53
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,840
both of you just drop it.

54
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,960
What?

55
00:03:53,961 --> 00:03:55,159
You know each other?

56
00:03:57,479 --> 00:03:58,319
Li Ming,

57
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,919
this is my friend Ouyang Han.

58
00:04:00,759 --> 00:04:01,520
Ouyang Han,
this is my friend

59
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,520
Li Ming.

60
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,359
We're all on the same side here.

61
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,895
Just consider this a
rough start to a friendship.

62
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,759
Who'd want to be friends with him?

63
00:04:12,199 --> 00:04:12,879
Next!

64
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:14,079
Instrument Group, Number 6.

65
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,920
Chen Ke from the Law
School, please get ready.

66
00:05:09,774 --> 00:05:10,841
[TN: Scoring rubric]

67
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,319
Now this is real music.

68
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,120
Chen Ke is the man.

69
00:05:33,319 --> 00:05:35,519
I guess even a gorilla can
appreciate the finer things.

70
00:05:36,279 --> 00:05:37,879
It's called art.

71
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,560
Like a poodle would know.

72
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:43,199
Yu Lei, how do you stand his
bad breath every single day?

73
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,839
You're the one with bad breath!

74
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,679
No, you!

75
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,800
You!

76
00:05:47,801 --> 00:05:49,959
I didn't realize Chen
Ke actually had talent.

77
00:05:50,439 --> 00:05:51,720
I totally underestimated him.

78
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,720
But why does that piece sound so familiar?

79
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,639
Have I heard it somewhere before?

80
00:06:00,959 --> 00:06:02,599
The list is out!

81
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,838
Look, Li Fei-hang and Chen Ke are on it.

82
00:06:03,839 --> 00:06:05,799
Wait, why is my roommate on there?

83
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,920
How did he make the cut?

84
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,680
I can't believe I'm not on the list.

85
00:06:09,879 --> 00:06:10,800
These judges

86
00:06:10,801 --> 00:06:12,480
have no taste.

87
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,240
Yu Lei,
you're right here.

88
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,560
Under the hosts.

89
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:21,360
Well, I guess they
aren't that blind after all.

90
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:25,920
Look,

91
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,160
Chen Ke.

92
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:29,839
No surprise there.

93
00:06:30,839 --> 00:06:31,800
I mean,

94
00:06:31,801 --> 00:06:32,959
he is actually good.

95
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:34,560
But still,

96
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:36,720
even if he's some piano prodigy,

97
00:06:36,959 --> 00:06:38,119
he's still not going to outshine

98
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,479
a handsome host

99
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,959
like me.

100
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,880
What's that supposed to mean?

101
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,360
Yu Lei?

102
00:07:49,399 --> 00:07:50,399
Were you looking for me?

103
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,518
No, I was just passing by.

104
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:54,160
I'm not...

105
00:07:54,161 --> 00:07:55,399
bothering you, am I?

106
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,680
Not at all.

107
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,920
By the way,

108
00:07:58,079 --> 00:07:59,439
is your foot all healed up?

109
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,599
It's been fine for a while.

110
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:09,680
Anyway,

111
00:08:09,681 --> 00:08:11,441
that piece you were
playing was really nice.

112
00:08:12,079 --> 00:08:13,079
What's it called?

113
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:14,879
This?
It's Beethoven's

114
00:08:15,601 --> 00:08:17,161
"Moonlight Sonata," the first movement.

115
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,120
Why? Do you like it?

116
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,880
I can lend you the tape sometime.

117
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,279
Oh, no, I couldn't...

118
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,439
I'd feel bad.

119
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:26,439
Well, actually,

120
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,560
how about I just make a copy
and give it right back?

121
00:08:29,319 --> 00:08:31,360
It's fine. It's hard to
find a kindred spirit.

122
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:32,279
Besides,

123
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,600
I've had this tape forever.

124
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,840
You can have it.

125
00:08:35,759 --> 00:08:36,878
Thanks, I appreciate it.

126
00:08:36,879 --> 00:08:37,879
So,

127
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,159
why were you asking about this piece?

128
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:41,559
I don't know.

129
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,255
I just feel like I've heard
it somewhere before.

130
00:08:43,279 --> 00:08:44,279
It's familiar,

131
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,279
but I can't place it.

132
00:08:48,159 --> 00:08:49,678
It feels like it has some kind of

133
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:50,679
special meaning to me.

134
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:52,519
Really?

135
00:08:52,879 --> 00:08:55,759
It has a special meaning to me, too.

136
00:09:02,039 --> 00:09:03,039
Grandma?

137
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,679
Where is that sound coming from?

138
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:10,000
It's coming from inside here.

139
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,200
Oh, I know!

140
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:14,080
There must be

141
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,959
a little person living inside.

142
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:18,119
And when I press this,

143
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,599
they start singing.

144
00:09:19,624 --> 00:09:20,823
You're so smart.

145
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,360
Here, press this button.

146
00:09:34,879 --> 00:09:36,200
That was my grandmother.

147
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,758
The "Moonlight Sonata"

148
00:09:37,759 --> 00:09:39,159
was her favorite piece.

149
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,881
She's the one who taught me
my very first song on the piano.

150
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:44,799
Oh, and

151
00:09:45,229 --> 00:09:46,655
she was a graduate of Ming De University, too.

152
00:09:46,679 --> 00:09:47,679
Really?

153
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,480
So she's an alumna!

154
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,840
So, where is she now?

155
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:54,439
Actually...

156
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,919
she passed away.

157
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,279
But I think

158
00:09:58,679 --> 00:10:00,440
if I can perform her favorite piece

159
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,559
on the stage here at Ming De University,

160
00:10:03,039 --> 00:10:04,199
maybe it'll make up for the fact

161
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,239
that she never got the chance

162
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,519
to perform here herself.

163
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:12,919
Anyway,

164
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:14,433
that was my grandma.

165
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:16,000
The "Moonlight Sonata."

166
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,440
I got it on tape.

167
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,240
It's okay.

168
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,200
Wait, what?

169
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,800
I can't believe you actually
talked to Chen Ke for that long.

170
00:10:27,279 --> 00:10:29,000
I thought you two were enemies.

171
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,039
We are.

172
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:32,820
But he helped me out before.

173
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,479
If I don't find a way

174
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,120
to return the favor,

175
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,640
I'll feel too guilty to
keep competing with him.

176
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,600
Whatever.

177
00:10:42,113 --> 00:10:43,593
Let's just call it a temporary truce.

178
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,159
Well, it's not like he's
competing with you.

179
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,960
Yu Lei!

180
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:49,320
Yu Lei! There you are.

181
00:10:49,321 --> 00:10:50,735
I've been looking everywhere for you.

182
00:10:50,759 --> 00:10:53,038
Here's the updated program
for the gala.

183
00:10:53,039 --> 00:10:54,359
There have been a lot of changes,

184
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:56,919
so we'll need to rewrite the intros.

185
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,840
Chen Ke's performance was cut.

186
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,960
Fine, let's do that.

187
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,360
Okay.

188
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:11,799
Sis?

189
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,158
You're the one who invited Chen Ke

190
00:11:13,159 --> 00:11:14,159
to the gala.

191
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,399
Why would you suddenly cut his performance?

192
00:11:16,559 --> 00:11:18,000
You have to give him an explanation.

193
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,319
I did invite him,

194
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,200
but cutting the act wasn't my decision.

195
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:23,758
We originally had

196
00:11:23,759 --> 00:11:24,918
two piano pieces

197
00:11:24,919 --> 00:11:26,320
and my violin solo.

198
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:29,158
The administration felt there
were too many instrumentals,

199
00:11:29,159 --> 00:11:30,320
so they decided to cut one.

200
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,758
But why'd they have to cut Chen Ke's?

201
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:33,799
Why not someone else's?

202
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:36,039
Why do you think?

203
00:11:36,879 --> 00:11:38,159
It's totally rigged!

204
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,080
Sis,

205
00:11:39,265 --> 00:11:41,066
you're the Student Union President.

206
00:11:41,159 --> 00:11:43,080
Can't you do something about this?

207
00:11:45,279 --> 00:11:47,159
Look, the administration
already made the call.

208
00:11:47,759 --> 00:11:48,480
But at least

209
00:11:48,481 --> 00:11:49,798
your hosting gig is safe.

210
00:11:49,799 --> 00:11:51,039
The higher-ups really like you.

211
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,720
Since when did you start
caring so much about this?

212
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,960
We're in the same class, that's all.

213
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:01,960
Anyway, I've gotta go.
See ya.

214
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,320
Okay.

215
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,560
Oh, I thought you guys weren't back yet.

216
00:12:22,759 --> 00:12:23,759
Perfect.

217
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,240
Were you looking for me?

218
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:28,678
Here, like I promised.

219
00:12:28,679 --> 00:12:29,200
Here.

220
00:12:29,639 --> 00:12:31,319
This is the recording my grandmother made.

221
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:32,600
No,

222
00:12:32,601 --> 00:12:34,361
I can't take this. It's
too precious to you.

223
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,399
It's fine.

224
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,599
I just made a copy for you.

225
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,600
Here.

226
00:12:38,559 --> 00:12:39,799
Thank you...

227
00:12:45,919 --> 00:12:47,639
Director, please reconsider.

228
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,279
That student really...

229
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:52,319
he's been practicing for so long.

230
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,360
Look, Yu Lei,

231
00:12:54,519 --> 00:12:56,439
this is the third time
you've come to see me.

232
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,879
I'll say it again:

233
00:12:58,039 --> 00:12:59,519
this isn't about personal preference.

234
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,479
It's about the big picture.

235
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,840
The big picture.

236
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,320
The big picture.

237
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,255
Does "the big picture" always have to come

238
00:13:06,279 --> 00:13:07,959
at someone else's expense?

239
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:08,960
Look,

240
00:13:08,961 --> 00:13:11,159
we have to keep the
show within the time limit.

241
00:13:11,639 --> 00:13:12,639
If you want

242
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,959
to add a segment,

243
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,639
we have to cut one.

244
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:16,919
So,

245
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:18,280
who do you suggest we cut instead?

246
00:13:19,399 --> 00:13:20,399
I...

247
00:13:20,519 --> 00:13:21,639
Let me think.

248
00:13:25,759 --> 00:13:27,678
I could step down as host.

249
00:13:27,679 --> 00:13:28,839
If there's one less host,

250
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,200
would that save enough time?

251
00:13:31,559 --> 00:13:32,639
Let me think about it.

252
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,440
Oh, good, you're here.

253
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,879
Here's the latest program.

254
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,879
Apparently, they changed it again.

255
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,600
They're unbelievable.

256
00:13:57,799 --> 00:13:58,918
Changing the script every day...

257
00:13:58,919 --> 00:13:59,720
I didn't even get to watch

258
00:13:59,721 --> 00:14:01,200
"Happy Camp" this weekend.

259
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,000
Yu Lei,

260
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:09,919
why are you so happy?

261
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,960
Isn't all this rewriting exhausting?

262
00:14:15,799 --> 00:14:17,759
Wait, why did it change
from a solo to a duet?

263
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,320
The production team felt

264
00:14:19,321 --> 00:14:20,558
the gala needed

265
00:14:20,559 --> 00:14:21,919
more variety.

266
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,239
That's why they decided

267
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:24,480
to have us perform together.

268
00:14:24,645 --> 00:14:26,006
Don't read too much into it.

269
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,320
No,

270
00:14:27,321 --> 00:14:30,254
actually, I'm just happy
I still get to perform.

271
00:14:30,656 --> 00:14:31,935
It's just...

272
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,129
I rarely play with others.

273
00:14:33,746 --> 00:14:35,306
I hope I don't mess up the performance.

274
00:14:35,556 --> 00:14:36,565
It'll be fine.

275
00:14:36,599 --> 00:14:37,960
We'll just practice a few times.

276
00:14:38,412 --> 00:14:40,351
I've prepared Chopin's
"Nocturne Op. 9 No. 2."

277
00:14:40,376 --> 00:14:43,405
Are you familiar with it? If not,
we can pick something else.

278
00:14:48,166 --> 00:14:49,246
I think I can manage.

279
00:14:49,512 --> 00:14:50,512
Great.

280
00:14:50,586 --> 00:14:52,798
Then let's try playing
it together now.

281
00:14:52,823 --> 00:14:54,464
- Okay.
- Let's see how it feels.

282
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,039
So,

283
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,319
why do you think Zhang Han

284
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,200
is perforMing De with a freshman?

285
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:25,919
Yu Lei,

286
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,519
are they really close?

287
00:15:27,799 --> 00:15:28,840
How should I know?

288
00:15:29,039 --> 00:15:30,079
Well, I heard

289
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:32,000
Chen Ke is a total heartthrob.

290
00:15:32,285 --> 00:15:34,405
And playing Chopin's "Nocturne" together?

291
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,440
There's definitely something

292
00:15:35,441 --> 00:15:36,599
going on between them.

293
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,360
Don't you think?

294
00:15:38,919 --> 00:15:40,200
Think what?

295
00:15:40,759 --> 00:15:41,918
Don't be dense.

296
00:15:41,919 --> 00:15:43,439
Look at Zhang Han...

297
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,639
she's beautiful

298
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,120
and a great violinist.

299
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,000
And Chen Ke?
He's handsome

300
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,320
and amazing on the piano.

301
00:15:50,159 --> 00:15:52,039
They're a match made in heaven.

302
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,239
When you play music like that together,

303
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,959
things are bound to happen.

304
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:55,519
No way.

305
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:56,840
Why not?

306
00:15:56,919 --> 00:15:58,360
It's totally impossible.

307
00:15:59,039 --> 00:16:00,320
There's an age gap!

308
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,878
Look at Nicholas Tse and Faye Wong...

309
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:03,320
they're ten years apart.

310
00:16:03,759 --> 00:16:06,039
And they're still going strong.

311
00:16:06,159 --> 00:16:07,199
It's so romantic.

312
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,440
I'm so jealous. I wish I had
someone to hold hands with...

313
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,080
And what are you two talking about?

314
00:16:12,279 --> 00:16:13,599
Don't get ahead of yourself.

315
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:15,280
We're just talking about celebrity gossip.

316
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,799
Oh, I see.

317
00:16:17,456 --> 00:16:18,854
Well, shall we?

318
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:20,480
And what do you think
it has to do with you?

319
00:16:21,039 --> 00:16:22,039
Come on.

320
00:16:51,799 --> 00:16:52,279
Good.

321
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:53,599
Oh, hello, Professor Meng.

322
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,119
Was our practicing too loud?

323
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,120
Did we disturb you?

324
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,200
No, not at all.

325
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:59,799
It sounded so beautiful

326
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,120
that I just found myself
following the music subconciously.

327
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,119
Sorry about that.

328
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,639
We'll keep it down next time.

329
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,880
Don't worry about it.

330
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:12,119
A scholar like me

331
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:14,518
shouldn't stay cooped up
in a study all day anyway.

332
00:17:14,519 --> 00:17:16,480
I need to know what's
going on in the world.

333
00:17:17,559 --> 00:17:18,480
Besides,

334
00:17:18,481 --> 00:17:21,599
what the two of you are
making is music, not noise.

335
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,079
By the way,

336
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,440
someone gave me these pastries,

337
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:29,160
but I can't eat them
because of my blood sugar.

338
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:34,559
So, I'm giving them to you two, as thanks
to both of you for the wonderful music.

339
00:17:35,359 --> 00:17:36,359
Here.

340
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:37,679
Thank you, Professor Meng.

341
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:38,680
You're very welcome.

342
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Sis!

343
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,119
Lei-lei...?
Come here.

344
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:02,960
Sis,

345
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,318
your violin solo

346
00:18:04,319 --> 00:18:06,359
is usually a school tradition, isn't it?

347
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,640
Why'd you change it to a duet with Chen Ke?

348
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,159
I had to make a small compromise

349
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,759
to keep everyone happy.

350
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,798
Besides, didn't you go to
the administration yourself?

351
00:18:17,799 --> 00:18:19,719
You were even willing to give up hosting

352
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,200
just to save Chen Ke's act.

353
00:18:21,759 --> 00:18:24,599
Isn't everyone happy this way?

354
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,200
That's only because he helped me out.

355
00:18:27,799 --> 00:18:28,599
I had to do something

356
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,240
to return the favor.

357
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,439
But that doesn't mean

358
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:34,160
you should have to lose out.

359
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Where is he, anyway?

360
00:18:37,359 --> 00:18:38,679
Why isn't he practicing with you?

361
00:18:38,839 --> 00:18:39,880
Is he throwing a fit?

362
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,480
You're overthinking things.

363
00:18:42,519 --> 00:18:44,079
I'm not losing out at all.

364
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:46,039
We've been practicing all afternoon;

365
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,119
he just had to step out for a bit.

366
00:18:49,799 --> 00:18:51,359
Well, at least he's being professional.

367
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,319
Actually,

368
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,799
I've had a bit of a surprise myself.

369
00:18:56,519 --> 00:18:57,719
I didn't expect

370
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:59,159
us to have such great chemistry

371
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,520
the first time we played together.

372
00:19:02,319 --> 00:19:03,079
So you two

373
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:04,799
are really in sync, huh?

374
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,799
He's also very dedicated

375
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,160
and works hard on his own.

376
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,240
You know,

377
00:19:10,599 --> 00:19:12,479
you could really learn
a thing or two from him.

378
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:14,319
Wait,

379
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,200
Sis, that's not fair.

380
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:19,319
Why do you always find a way to
praise him while putting me down?

381
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:22,926
I'm dedicated too!

382
00:19:23,519 --> 00:19:26,995
Besides, what's so great about
being wound up like that all the time?

383
00:19:27,646 --> 00:19:31,456
You need to strike a balance
between work and play.

384
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,039
You have a point.

385
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:36,719
Actually, the school is
showing a movie tonight.

386
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:38,440
I bought two tickets

387
00:19:38,759 --> 00:19:41,039
and was planning to invite Chen Ke.

388
00:19:41,759 --> 00:19:43,240
I thought it would help him relax.

389
00:19:43,839 --> 00:19:44,839
What?

390
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,480
You're taking him to a movie?

391
00:19:48,119 --> 00:19:50,119
That's basically a date!

392
00:19:50,279 --> 00:19:50,680
Sis,

393
00:19:50,681 --> 00:19:52,159
don't tell me you're trying
to be like Faye Wong.

394
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,416
You're not actually into
younger guys, are you?

395
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,559
This is crazy.

396
00:19:54,799 --> 00:19:56,200
- That's too much.
- Yu Lei!

397
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,015
Aren't you supposed to be
a modern college student?

398
00:19:59,039 --> 00:20:00,278
It's just a movie.

399
00:20:00,279 --> 00:20:01,519
That doesn't mean we're dating.

400
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,479
What's wrong with a senior

401
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,519
looking out for a junior?

402
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,839
Everything is wrong with it!

403
00:20:08,279 --> 00:20:09,039
President!
President!

404
00:20:10,079 --> 00:20:11,616
The committee has some urgent business.

405
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:14,440
They want to meet with
our department tonight.

406
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,239
Tonight?

407
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:16,720
Yeah.
I...

408
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:19,440
Sis, Sis!

409
00:20:19,839 --> 00:20:21,639
How about I go to the movie instead?

410
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:22,640
The tickets are already bought,

411
00:20:22,641 --> 00:20:24,000
it'd be a waste not to use them.

412
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,440
Fine.

413
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,079
I guess I'll let you have them.

414
00:20:29,119 --> 00:20:30,119
Lucky you.

415
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:31,680
Great!

416
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:33,480
Thanks, Sis.

417
00:20:33,505 --> 00:20:35,753
(Student's Club)

418
00:20:53,279 --> 00:20:54,960
Why isn't senior here yet?

419
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:03,440
Hey, Bo Ya.

420
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:04,920
Waiting for your Ziqi?

421
00:21:04,945 --> 00:21:06,294
[Reference to the classic story of musicians
and "best friends" Bo Ya and Zhong Ziqi]

422
00:21:06,319 --> 00:21:07,480
What are you talking about?

423
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,159
You know, "High Mountains
and Flowing Water."

424
00:21:11,184 --> 00:21:12,583
Bo Ya and Ziqi.

425
00:21:12,799 --> 00:21:14,439
Aren't you and my sister

426
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,799
like kindred spirits?

427
00:21:16,519 --> 00:21:17,799
If you're Bo Ya,

428
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:19,160
then she must be your Ziqi.

429
00:21:22,319 --> 00:21:27,160
Musically speaking,
I think we do have a certain connection.

430
00:21:27,559 --> 00:21:29,039
But as for anything else...

431
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:32,240
I wouldn't go as far
as calling us soulmates.

432
00:21:34,279 --> 00:21:35,279
What about me?

433
00:21:35,319 --> 00:21:36,680
Do I qualify as your Ziqi?

434
00:21:38,359 --> 00:21:39,359
You're unbelievable.

435
00:21:41,119 --> 00:21:41,880
Anyway,

436
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,000
I'll stop teasing.

437
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,200
My sister had something
come up at the last minute,

438
00:21:45,359 --> 00:21:46,640
so she gave me her ticket.

439
00:21:47,079 --> 00:21:48,359
Come on, let's watch the movie.

440
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,240
Chen Ke,

441
00:22:28,559 --> 00:22:30,640
you always act so serious.

442
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:31,759
I can't believe

443
00:22:31,799 --> 00:22:33,239
you actually cried during the movie.

444
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,359
Look at your red nose!

445
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:37,598
You were sobbing too.

446
00:22:37,599 --> 00:22:38,680
I heard you.

447
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:41,519
I wasn't nearly as bad as you.

448
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:42,400
You were

449
00:22:42,519 --> 00:22:43,519
twitching

450
00:22:43,839 --> 00:22:45,000
like a little squirrel.

451
00:22:45,799 --> 00:22:46,839
Get the hell out of here.

452
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,240
If I'm a squirrel,

453
00:22:48,279 --> 00:22:49,279
then what are you?

454
00:22:49,599 --> 00:22:51,119
A devious old fox?

455
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,200
Me?

456
00:22:52,519 --> 00:22:54,559
How am I an old fox?

457
00:22:55,119 --> 00:22:57,160
During that scene in the car,

458
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,440
I didn't even know what was going on yet,

459
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,920
but you were already laughing.

460
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,598
You've got a dirty mind.

461
00:23:03,599 --> 00:23:05,160
And you say you're not an old fox?

462
00:23:07,119 --> 00:23:09,640
You're a pretty good-looking guy.

463
00:23:10,359 --> 00:23:11,919
Have you really never had a girlfriend?

464
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,839
I don't buy that you're this innocent.

465
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:16,039
It's not anything like that.

466
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:17,799
I've only ever had one girlfriend.

467
00:23:18,079 --> 00:23:19,279
We didn't even kiss.

468
00:23:19,799 --> 00:23:21,599
The most we did was hold hands.

469
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,240
Love?

470
00:23:23,662 --> 00:23:25,000
I don't think it was really love.

471
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:27,839
It was probably just curiosity
about the opposite sex.

472
00:23:42,559 --> 00:23:43,599
Alright, level with me.

473
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:45,880
Is there a girl you like right now?

474
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:47,799
Right now?

475
00:23:48,799 --> 00:23:49,960
Not at the moment.

476
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,960
Well,

477
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:55,279
what's your type, then?

478
00:23:56,519 --> 00:23:57,519
I think...

479
00:23:57,520 --> 00:23:59,200
we'd need to have common interests.

480
00:23:59,519 --> 00:24:02,240
A genuine, mutual
attraction from the heart.

481
00:24:03,799 --> 00:24:04,799
So...

482
00:24:05,039 --> 00:24:06,359
what do you think of my sister?

483
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,880
Why are you asking me that?

484
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,078
Didn't you say the other day

485
00:24:10,079 --> 00:24:11,358
that whoever lost the game

486
00:24:11,359 --> 00:24:12,759
wouldn't talk to her?

487
00:24:13,799 --> 00:24:15,640
I was just joking then.

488
00:24:16,799 --> 00:24:18,640
I'm just using her as an example.

489
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:20,039
So all that time

490
00:24:20,319 --> 00:24:22,039
you were targeting me,

491
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,440
it was because you were
worried about me and your sister?

492
00:24:25,359 --> 00:24:26,359
Don't worry.

493
00:24:26,559 --> 00:24:27,559
It's not like that.

494
00:24:27,599 --> 00:24:29,039
She's amazing,

495
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:32,279
but I just
don't feel that way about her.

496
00:24:34,759 --> 00:24:35,759
What way?

497
00:24:38,359 --> 00:24:40,439
I remember a writer once said:

498
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:41,599
"To me, love

499
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,936
isn't just about physical intimacy

500
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:43,960
or sharing a meal.

501
00:24:44,599 --> 00:24:46,079
It's an undying desire...

502
00:24:46,519 --> 00:24:48,440
a heroic dream in a weary life."

503
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,160
I've always loved that quote.

504
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,720
I think that's what love should be.

505
00:24:53,079 --> 00:24:54,079
Something sacred.

506
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,599
That's the "feeling"

507
00:24:57,079 --> 00:24:58,319
I'm talking about.

508
00:25:01,839 --> 00:25:02,799
I think

509
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:03,999
that's true for everyone,

510
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,359
throughout history.

511
00:25:06,519 --> 00:25:07,719
It's like they say:

512
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,959
"They talk of a match
made in gold and jade,

513
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:12,200
but I only dream of the old
alliance of wood and stone."

514
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:14,656
A lot of people who read
"Dream of the Red Chamber"

515
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,199
think Xue Bao-chai is smart

516
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:17,240
and proper,

517
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:19,359
so she's the best match for Jia Bao-yu.

518
00:25:20,799 --> 00:25:21,799
But I don't think so.

519
00:25:22,039 --> 00:25:23,039
Exactly.

520
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:26,160
Bao-yu and Dai-yu are the
ones who truly belong together.

521
00:25:26,279 --> 00:25:28,720
They have a real soul connection.

522
00:25:29,119 --> 00:25:32,440
Some of those sequels that
force Bao-chai and Bao-yu together

523
00:25:33,039 --> 00:25:35,119
completely miss the point.

524
00:25:35,319 --> 00:25:36,000
Yeah.

525
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:38,159
If Cao Xueqin knew,

526
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:40,000
he'd probably want to take them all out.

527
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,920
He wasn't that hot-headed.

528
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,680
But

529
00:25:46,079 --> 00:25:47,319
speaking of souls...

530
00:25:48,119 --> 00:25:50,279
how do you actually see someone's soul?

531
00:25:51,765 --> 00:25:53,166
Maybe it's because

532
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:55,039
souls are so hard to see

533
00:25:55,799 --> 00:26:01,319
so people have always
lamented how rare true love is.

534
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:06,160
When someone has something
on their mind, they frown.

535
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,280
Just like you're doing right now.

536
00:26:09,799 --> 00:26:11,160
I think seeing that frown...

537
00:26:11,359 --> 00:26:13,039
is like seeing into someone's soul.

538
00:26:13,759 --> 00:26:14,799
You're right.

539
00:26:15,519 --> 00:26:17,200
I think that's it.

540
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,680
And I believe

541
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:21,440
that beautiful souls are
naturally drawn to each other.

542
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:24,480
They just keep getting closer.

543
00:26:24,839 --> 00:26:25,839
It's like that poem:

544
00:26:26,279 --> 00:26:28,440
"You're from Yunnan, Yuanmou,

545
00:26:29,759 --> 00:26:31,680
I'm from Beijing, Zhoukou.

546
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,920
We reach out our furry hands...

547
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:34,960
and it's love

548
00:26:35,079 --> 00:26:37,440
that makes us walk upright like a pole."

549
00:26:41,799 --> 00:26:42,519
Chen Ke,

550
00:26:42,647 --> 00:26:43,727
I hope everything goes well.

551
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:45,119
Wait, no.

552
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:47,359
I mean... I hope the
performance is a huge success.

553
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,160
It will be.

554
00:27:00,799 --> 00:27:03,119
September 2000. Sunny.

555
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,519
Every day is busy and fulfilling.

556
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:08,559
New people, new experiences...

557
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,519
my schedule is packed.

558
00:27:11,759 --> 00:27:14,640
As the performance draws closer,
I'm getting more and more excited.

559
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:17,839
Not just to fulfill my grandmother's wish,

560
00:27:18,599 --> 00:27:20,640
but also to live up to
everyone's expectations.

561
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:22,799
Like the senior...

562
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:25,038
Professor Meng...

563
00:27:25,039 --> 00:27:26,039
and

564
00:27:26,519 --> 00:27:27,519
Yu Lei.

565
00:28:00,279 --> 00:28:01,359
Get out of my way.

566
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,440
You're so childish.

567
00:28:12,079 --> 00:28:12,759
Chen Ke,

568
00:28:12,839 --> 00:28:14,039
you're up next.

569
00:28:14,519 --> 00:28:15,519
Good luck!

570
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,599
Chen Ke, it's time for you to go on.

571
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:04,960
"You ask me how deep my love is..."

572
00:31:05,079 --> 00:31:06,519
"I love you as much as—"

573
00:31:06,559 --> 00:31:07,519
Meng-yu, stop singing!
Have a drink first. Here we go.

574
00:31:08,241 --> 00:31:09,696
We'll have plenty of time for that later.

575
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:10,519
Come on.

576
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,439
Let's all have a drink together.

577
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,720
Cheers! Come on.

578
00:31:13,839 --> 00:31:14,640
Everyone!
Cheers!

579
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:16,839
Cheers!

580
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:23,000
Bottoms up!

581
00:31:23,319 --> 00:31:24,000
Chen Ke,

582
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,480
you did a great job at the gala.

583
00:31:27,119 --> 00:31:29,200
Senior, I'm the one who
should be thanking you.

584
00:31:29,359 --> 00:31:30,480
Sis!

585
00:31:30,599 --> 00:31:32,200
Why are you only praising Chen Ke?

586
00:31:32,359 --> 00:31:34,000
You didn't even mention my contribution.

587
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:36,535
Oh, right. Chen Ke, you
probably didn't know this,

588
00:31:36,559 --> 00:31:37,480
but the administration

589
00:31:37,481 --> 00:31:39,640
almost cut your piano piece.

590
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,358
It was all thanks to our Lei-lei.

591
00:31:41,359 --> 00:31:42,879
He fought so hard for you.

592
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:43,680
That's the only reason

593
00:31:43,681 --> 00:31:45,000
we got to perform together.

594
00:31:45,079 --> 00:31:46,735
If you're going to thank anyone, thank him.

595
00:31:46,759 --> 00:31:48,279
Well, thank you both, then.

596
00:31:50,079 --> 00:31:51,079
Easy there.

597
00:31:51,559 --> 00:31:52,959
Wow, look at him go.

598
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:54,920
Nice! Take it easy.

599
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:56,440
You okay?
I'm fine.

600
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,839
Sis, I can handle this.

601
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:04,999
You're being way too sincere.

602
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,000
You're such a good kid.

603
00:32:06,759 --> 00:32:07,519
Yu Lei,
I want to thank you

604
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:09,600
on behalf of my grandmother, too.

605
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:12,240
Don't mention it.

606
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:15,000
Director!

607
00:32:15,001 --> 00:32:16,798
We all worked hard, too.

608
00:32:16,799 --> 00:32:18,519
Why are you only paying attention to them?

609
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:20,480
One at a time, Meng-yu.

610
00:32:20,519 --> 00:32:21,599
You were great, too.

611
00:32:21,839 --> 00:32:22,519
Tell you what...

612
00:32:22,759 --> 00:32:24,519
National Day is coming up.

613
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:26,200
Let's all go on a trip together.

614
00:32:26,279 --> 00:32:27,240
Anyone who's free can come,

615
00:32:27,241 --> 00:32:28,281
and you can bring friends.

616
00:32:28,319 --> 00:32:29,119
Sounds good!

617
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:30,199
Long live the senior!

618
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,278
Come on, everyone!

619
00:32:31,279 --> 00:32:31,880
Let's go!
Trip time!

620
00:32:32,721 --> 00:32:34,160
Cheers!

621
00:32:46,096 --> 00:32:51,590
(Ming [De] University celebrates
the National Day holiday)

622
00:32:53,559 --> 00:32:55,440
Wow, he's so handsome!

623
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:56,680
Look.

624
00:32:57,279 --> 00:32:58,319
Isn't he handsome?

625
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:00,838
Here, you can have this one.

626
00:33:00,839 --> 00:33:02,039
This one's really cool, too.

627
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:03,160
No way!

628
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:04,480
Which one do you like best?
Why are you being like that?

629
00:33:05,319 --> 00:33:06,160
You're so stingy.
Look at this one.

630
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,519
Stingy?

631
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,078
I think you're the one with the nerve

632
00:33:10,079 --> 00:33:11,119
to just tag along.

633
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:13,680
I have no idea why you even came.

634
00:33:14,599 --> 00:33:16,318
Hey, I helped set up the stage

635
00:33:16,319 --> 00:33:17,440
for the school, okay?

636
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,880
Why shouldn't I be allowed to come?

637
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,240
Besides,

638
00:33:23,519 --> 00:33:25,039
there are plenty of pretty girls here.

639
00:33:25,200 --> 00:33:26,480
Isn't that why you're here, too?

640
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,880
You're delusional.

641
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:30,639
You think everyone is
as girl-crazy as you are?

642
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:31,640
Pervert.

643
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,519
Yu Lei invited me.

644
00:33:34,759 --> 00:33:36,039
I'm basically family.

645
00:33:37,359 --> 00:33:39,200
Family?

646
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,440
You look more like a rat to me.

647
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,480
You...

648
00:33:44,839 --> 00:33:45,839
Yu Lei! Hey.

649
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:51,319
Yu Lei, how are we splitting up the rooms

650
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:52,519
at the guesthouse?

651
00:33:53,319 --> 00:33:55,240
Senior, why don't we share a room?

652
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:56,480
Sounds good.

653
00:33:57,839 --> 00:33:58,240
Yu Lei!

654
00:33:58,241 --> 00:33:59,559
Let's share a room.

655
00:34:00,839 --> 00:34:01,839
Sorry,

656
00:34:02,039 --> 00:34:03,078
I already told Chen Ke

657
00:34:03,079 --> 00:34:04,079
I'd stay with him.

658
00:34:05,319 --> 00:34:06,599
Wait, when did we agree to that?

659
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:14,239
Chen Ke keeps saying he
doesn't have feelings for my sister,

660
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:16,079
but you never know.

661
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,638
During this trip,

662
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:18,999
I need to keep a close eye on him.

663
00:34:20,119 --> 00:34:21,719
Our bus is here. Let's go.

664
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:23,920
Let's go, let's go! Let's go, let's go!

665
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:28,080
Looks like you've been dumped.

666
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:29,360
Feeling a bit left out?

667
00:34:29,639 --> 00:34:30,639
Get lost.

668
00:34:32,159 --> 00:34:32,960
Fine.

669
00:34:33,015 --> 00:34:34,494
I'll be generous

670
00:34:34,519 --> 00:34:35,639
and let you stay in my room.

671
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:38,320
You must be dreaming.

672
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:39,879
Who knows if you snore

673
00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:40,880
like crazy?

674
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:43,880
You're so ungrateful.

675
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:45,880
Just get in there.
Stop stalling.

676
00:36:35,679 --> 00:36:36,320
Yu Lei!

677
00:36:36,599 --> 00:36:38,159
What took you so long in the shower?

678
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
Was I that long?

679
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:42,800
It's your turn.

680
00:36:46,599 --> 00:36:47,960
Why didn't you dry your hair?

681
00:36:48,519 --> 00:36:49,199
There's a fan right there.

682
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:50,360
You're going to catch a cold.

683
00:36:51,519 --> 00:36:53,679
It's fine. I'll just let it air dry.

684
00:36:54,559 --> 00:36:55,840
You can't do that.

685
00:37:00,119 --> 00:37:01,119
Yu Lei!

686
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:04,615
You guys have to let me stay here tonight,

687
00:37:04,639 --> 00:37:06,119
or I'm not going to make it.

688
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,519
What's wrong now?

689
00:37:07,719 --> 00:37:08,719
Li Ming!

690
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,759
He was out the second
his head hit the pillow.

691
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:12,158
And he snores!

692
00:37:12,159 --> 00:37:13,760
It sounds like a thunderstorm in there.

693
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:16,719
I think I'm going deaf.

694
00:37:17,639 --> 00:37:18,639
But...

695
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:20,359
this is just a single bed.

696
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,760
It's not big enough for two people.

697
00:37:23,039 --> 00:37:24,039
I promise

698
00:37:24,239 --> 00:37:25,678
I'll be good.

699
00:37:25,679 --> 00:37:26,719
I won't even move.

700
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:28,638
Just let me crash here for one night.

701
00:37:28,639 --> 00:37:30,239
Please, Yu Lei?

702
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:33,599
What about the sofa in the living room?

703
00:37:33,679 --> 00:37:36,119
I already checked.
It's too drafty out there.

704
00:37:37,599 --> 00:37:38,599
Tell you what...

705
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:39,960
you two take the room,

706
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,999
and I'll go sleep on the sofa.

707
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:43,239
- Okay.
- No way.

708
00:37:50,639 --> 00:37:51,639
I'll go.

709
00:38:13,586 --> 00:38:16,446
(Museum of Cinema)

710
00:38:33,199 --> 00:38:34,000
What?

711
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,336
What's this?
Out for an early walk without telling me?

712
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:37,678
Look at those dark circles.

713
00:38:37,679 --> 00:38:38,679
Didn't you sleep well?

714
00:38:39,719 --> 00:38:40,760
Don't even get me started.

715
00:38:41,039 --> 00:38:41,960
I spent all night

716
00:38:41,961 --> 00:38:43,360
in the living room shivering.

717
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:45,640
I only managed to catch a
few minutes of sleep at dawn.

718
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:50,760
What about you?

719
00:38:50,761 --> 00:38:52,481
You look like you didn't sleep much either.

720
00:38:52,559 --> 00:38:55,639
I always have trouble sleeping
in a new environment.

721
00:38:56,121 --> 00:38:58,065
Plus, Ouyang Han
wouldn't stop talking to me.

722
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:00,439
Honestly,

723
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,719
I really envy you sometimes.

724
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:03,280
You have so many good friends,

725
00:39:03,719 --> 00:39:05,199
and they're all so full of life.

726
00:39:06,159 --> 00:39:07,159
Not like me.

727
00:39:11,199 --> 00:39:12,679
It's raining! Let's go.

728
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,000
Oh, man.

729
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:33,000
We were planning on going for a hike today.

730
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:34,920
I guess that's not happening.

731
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:11,119
Damn.

732
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:13,159
It looks like it's really
starting to come down.

733
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,800
Let's just run for it!

734
00:40:22,087 --> 00:40:23,087
Come on!

735
00:40:32,079 --> 00:40:34,239
Cheers!

736
00:40:37,239 --> 00:40:38,559
This is actually really good.

737
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:40,280
Is it ready yet? Let me see.
Is it boiling?

738
00:40:40,761 --> 00:40:41,799
The water isn't boiling yet.

739
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:42,800
We can't put the food in.

740
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,559
Not yet.

741
00:40:43,560 --> 00:40:44,599
Just wait a bit.

742
00:40:45,679 --> 00:40:46,400
How about

743
00:40:46,401 --> 00:40:47,799
we watch a movie first?

744
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:48,800
Sure.
What do you have?

745
00:40:50,039 --> 00:40:51,159
Any Hollywood blockbusters?

746
00:40:51,519 --> 00:40:53,638
I heard "Mission:
Impossible 2" is really good.

747
00:40:53,639 --> 00:40:56,359
Tom Cruise is so hot.

748
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:57,599
I don't have that.

749
00:40:58,880 --> 00:40:59,880
But I do have this.

750
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,119
Why don't we watch this?

751
00:41:01,144 --> 00:41:02,100
["Happy Together" dir. Wong Kar-wai, one of
the most depressing gay movies ever made]

752
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,960
It's got Leslie Cheung and Tony Leung.

753
00:41:05,039 --> 00:41:06,198
There are a lot of stars in it.

754
00:41:06,199 --> 00:41:07,599
Sounds good! Let's do it.

755
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:14,880
Put the food in!

756
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:15,920
Okay.

757
00:41:30,039 --> 00:41:31,480
Wait... is this a porno?

758
00:41:35,079 --> 00:41:36,360
Why are there two guys?

759
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:39,040
Leslie Cheung and Tony Leung were in this?

760
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:42,440
Did the shopkeeper give us the wrong tape?

761
00:41:43,199 --> 00:41:44,360
I thought...

762
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:53,279
Hey, why don't we just watch this instead?

763
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:54,960
"King of Comedy." It'll be more fun.

764
00:41:56,199 --> 00:41:58,320
Yeah, "King of Comedy" is great.

765
00:42:00,719 --> 00:42:02,000
Hurry up, Yu Lei!

766
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,360
Come on, Yu Lei.

767
00:42:04,159 --> 00:42:05,159
Cheers!

768
00:42:05,239 --> 00:42:06,239
Cheers!

769
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:37,679
Why'd you stop eating?

770
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:39,519
I don't know.

771
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:42,320
Between the beer and the hot pot...

772
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:43,960
Look.

773
00:42:44,119 --> 00:42:45,839
I feel like my stomach is about to explode.

774
00:42:46,159 --> 00:42:47,159
That's ridiculous.

775
00:42:48,599 --> 00:42:49,719
You don't have a stomach.

776
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,039
Those are abs.

777
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:02,440
Yu Lei...

778
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:06,039
do you ever feel like I'm not normal?

779
00:43:07,280 --> 00:43:09,119
Everyone else is out chasing the sun,

780
00:43:09,719 --> 00:43:10,719
but I...

781
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,719
I'm always alone in the dark.

782
00:43:15,239 --> 00:43:16,239
Chen Ke,

783
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:17,679
what are you talking about?

784
00:43:19,599 --> 00:43:20,599
Yu Lei,

785
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:21,880
you know...

786
00:43:22,679 --> 00:43:23,880
when I was a kid,

787
00:43:24,239 --> 00:43:25,679
it was just me and my grandmother.

788
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,159
Between practicing and competitions,

789
00:43:29,199 --> 00:43:31,440
I never had time to talk
to people my own age.

790
00:43:32,159 --> 00:43:33,159
I didn't even know

791
00:43:33,280 --> 00:43:35,239
how to act around other kids.

792
00:43:36,519 --> 00:43:37,719
After a while,

793
00:43:38,159 --> 00:43:39,559
I just got used to being by myself.

794
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:42,440
So...

795
00:43:42,519 --> 00:43:44,599
I've been following you
around this whole time.

796
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:47,480
Do you... do you find me annoying?

797
00:43:51,159 --> 00:43:52,320
Get drunk!

798
00:43:52,639 --> 00:43:53,960
Let's go.

799
00:43:57,280 --> 00:43:58,280
No.

800
00:43:58,760 --> 00:44:00,039
Actually, I like it.

801
00:44:00,639 --> 00:44:03,320
I'm happy to tell you about myself.

802
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:06,719
I even find myself thinking...

803
00:44:07,119 --> 00:44:09,039
that I wish I'd met you sooner.

804
00:44:09,159 --> 00:44:10,079
Maybe then...

805
00:44:10,080 --> 00:44:12,320
I wouldn't have spent my
whole life without any friends.

806
00:44:16,679 --> 00:44:17,679
Chen Ke...

807
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:18,920
I'm sorry.

808
00:44:19,039 --> 00:44:20,079
To be honest...

809
00:44:22,840 --> 00:44:23,599
to be honest...

810
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:25,158
I used to think

811
00:44:25,159 --> 00:44:27,239
you were just this cold, difficult person.

812
00:44:27,719 --> 00:44:29,960
That's why I couldn't stand you.

813
00:44:31,039 --> 00:44:32,840
But then I realized...

814
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,480
that's not who you are at all.

815
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:37,840
It's okay.

816
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:40,800
I'm used to people getting
the wrong idea about me.

817
00:44:42,159 --> 00:44:43,599
I always felt like

818
00:44:44,039 --> 00:44:47,320
people would come and go,

819
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:50,119
and in the end, I'd always be alone.

820
00:44:51,559 --> 00:44:52,920
But when I'm with you...

821
00:44:53,599 --> 00:44:55,000
I don't feel that way.

822
00:45:05,519 --> 00:45:06,519
Look.

823
00:45:06,639 --> 00:45:08,880
Even the rain has taken on meaning now.

824
00:45:14,840 --> 00:45:15,840
Yu Lei...

825
00:45:17,119 --> 00:45:20,320
can I consider you my friend?

826
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:24,000
No.

827
00:45:24,079 --> 00:45:25,679
My best friend.

828
00:45:27,480 --> 00:45:28,639
Is that okay?

829
00:45:31,760 --> 00:45:32,760
Sure.

830
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:35,480
Pinky swear.

831
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:43,800
Chen Ke...

832
00:46:43,840 --> 00:46:44,840
That night,

833
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:48,119
I couldn't take my eyes off Chen Ke's face.

834
00:46:48,800 --> 00:46:51,039
I suddenly realized
how cute he actually was.

835
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:54,000
I felt this sudden urge
to be even closer to him.

836
00:46:55,360 --> 00:46:57,280
It was only later that it finally clicked.

837
00:46:58,519 --> 00:47:00,919
- That was the moment I started falling for him.
- Goodnight.

838
00:47:05,400 --> 00:47:07,279
(Next Episode Preview)
Lately, you and Chen Ke

839
00:47:07,280 --> 00:47:08,880
have been joined at the hip, haven't you?

840
00:47:09,840 --> 00:47:11,680
I thought you'd completely
forgotten about me.

841
00:47:12,239 --> 00:47:14,840
Do you want to try the pose I mentioned?

842
00:47:15,920 --> 00:47:17,000
What pose?

843
00:47:18,719 --> 00:47:20,199
Are you free on Christmas?

844
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:21,480
I...

845
00:47:22,599 --> 00:47:23,920
Christmas?

846
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:25,800
I... might have some plans of my own.

847
00:47:26,280 --> 00:47:29,159
Is romance the only way to be intimate?

848
00:47:29,639 --> 00:47:33,159
Can't friends, brothers,
or family be close, too?

849
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:34,600
Can't we express that physically?

